text: HarringayThe neighbourhood of Harringay is spelt with two r's and two a's whereas the borough of Haringey is spelt with one r and one a. (pronounced ) is a housing area in the London Borough of Haringey in north London, in England. It is centred on the section of Green Lanes running between the New River, where it crosses Green Lanes by Finsbury Park, and Duckett's Common, near Turnpike Lane. ==References== Category:District and borough councils in England Category:Areas of London Category:London Borough of Haringey
title: Harringay
